## 1. рҹҺҜ Product Vision

**Attenza** is a student-led, offline-first classroom attendance management app built for college classes.

### What makes it different:
- Attendance is taken by **CR (Class Representative)** and **LR (Lady Representative)** вҖ” NOT faculty
- Students are **auto-assigned** to their class using roll numbers
- Works **fully offline** вҖ” syncs to cloud when internet is available
- **Roll numbers** are the central identity of the entire system
- Designed for **VIT-AP College** (scalable to multi-college later)

### Core Philosophy:
> "App never waits for the server. Everything happens locally first. Server is just for sync & backup."

---

## 2. рҹ‘Ҙ User Roles & Capabilities

There are **4 roles** in Attenza:

### 2.1 CR вҖ” Class Representative
| Capability | Allowed |
|-----------|---------|
| Create class structure | вң… |
| Define roll number range | вң… |
| Create subjects (class/lab) | вң… |
| Take attendance | вң… |
| Edit attendance | вң… |
| Delete attendance | вң… |
| View & search history | вң… |
| Share attendance (WhatsApp/Copy) | вң… |
| Transfer CR role | вң… |

### 2.2 LR вҖ” Lady Representative
- **Identical permissions to CR**
- Fully synced with CR вҖ” any change by one instantly reflects on the other
- Only one CR and one LR per class

### 2.3 Student
| Capability | Allowed |
|-----------|---------|
| View own attendance % | вң… |
| View subject-wise breakdown (graph) | вң… |
| View history (scroll) | вң… |
| Copy attendance summary | вң… |
| Edit own name | вң… |
| Take attendance | вқҢ |
| Edit/Delete attendance | вқҢ |
| Search/filter history | вқҢ |
| Create subjects | вқҢ |

### 2.4 Admin
| Capability | Allowed |
|-----------|---------|
| Convert Student вҶ” CR | вң… |
| Assign / Remove CR or LR | вң… |
| View all users (CR/LR/Students) | вң… |
| View all classes and their status | вң… |
| Monitor attendance stats system-wide | вң… |
| Resolve role conflicts after verification | вң… |
| View admin activity logs | вң… |
| Delete or archive classes | вң… |

> **Admin Note:** Admin is a separate credential (not through the mobile app вҖ” via a web dashboard or special admin-only screen). Architecture must support admin actions from day one, even if the UI is built in Phase 2.

